.TH PERPLEXITY-RESEARCHER 1 "November 2025" "1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
perplexity-researcher \- AI-powered research automation tool using Perplexity.ai
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B perplexity-researcher
.I command
[
.I arguments
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B perplexity-researcher
is a command-line tool that automates interactions with Perplexity.ai. It allows you to perform research queries and save the results locally. It uses a persistent browser session to maintain authentication state.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B auth
Opens a browser window for you to log in to Perplexity.ai.
.br
Once logged in, close the browser window. Your session cookies and local storage will be saved to \fB~/.config/perplexity-researcher/browser-data\fR.
.br
You only need to run this once, or whenever your session expires.

.TP
.B query "\fIquestion\fR"
Runs a single research query.
.br
The tool will launch a browser (visible by default), navigate to Perplexity, input your question, wait for the answer to generate, and save the result.
.br
.B Example:
.br
\fBperplexity-researcher query "What is the history of the internet?"\fR

.TP
.B query
(Without arguments)
.br
Reads queries from a \fBqueries.json\fR file in the current directory.
.br
The file must contain a JSON array of strings.
.br
.B Example queries.json:
.br
["What is quantum computing?", "Who won the 1994 World Cup?"]

.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/perplexity-researcher/browser-data
Directory where browser profile (cookies, cache) is stored.
.TP
.B ./perplexity_results/
Directory where query results are saved as JSON files. Created in the current working directory.
.TP
.B ./queries.json
Optional input file for batch queries.

.SH NOTES
.IP \[bu] 2
The tool uses Playwright with a headful (visible) browser by default to avoid detection.
.IP \[bu]
Do not interact with the browser window while the query is running, as it might interfere with the automation.

